00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:24,260
They don't have to be.

289
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,560
They could be any set

290
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,620
of coordinates describing a physical system.

291
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,200
In particular,

292
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:32,100
they could be the values of

293
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,000
fields at different places in space.

294
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,000
But we'll come to that.

295
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,440
Whatever those coordinates are that

296
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:39,520
describe the state of a system,

297
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:40,920
the configuration of a system,

298
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,780
we combine them together,

299
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,580
and we call them the set of variables Q.

300
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,160
Now,

301
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,340
in the simple situations that we're familiar with,

302
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:53,620
there typically are several Qs,

303
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:54,780
more than one of them.

304
00:12:55,060 --> 00:12:57,780
The Qs could stand for the positions of particles.

305
00:12:58,460 --> 00:13:02,900
If there are n particles moving on a line,

306
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:05,420
all the particles moving on the same line,

307
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,180
then there are n coordinates,

308
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:08,620
and we might call them x.

309
00:13:09,660 --> 00:13:11,240
I don't want to call them x now.

310
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:13,410
The reason I'm calling them Q is because x

311
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:15,440
is going to have some other significance for us.

312
00:13:17,439 --> 00:13:21,220
But some number of coordinates Q,

313
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:24,400
it could be a single particle moving in three dimensions.

314
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,480
Then there are three Qs.

315
00:13:26,620 --> 00:13:27,220
In fact,

316
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,680
there would be three Qs,

317
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:29,240
x,

318
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:29,580
y,

319
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:29,980
and z,

320
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:32,220
for a particle moving in three dimensions.

321
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,820
There would be three Qs if there

322
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:37,020
were three particles all moving in one dimension.

323
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:39,500
So the fact that there are three Qs,

324
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:40,660
and not seven Qs,

325
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:41,800
or fourteen Qs,

326
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,740
or ten Qs,

327
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,100
doesn't necessarily tell you how

328
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,800
many dimensional problems you're working in,

329
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:49,100
but it does tell you how many

330
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:51,280
coordinates it takes to describe a system.

331
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:54,060
So we could label them Q sub i,

332
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:56,640
where i runs from one to anything.

333
00:13:57,060 --> 00:14:00,960
We could even imagine systems of infinitely many particles.

334
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:05,300
We might get a little

335
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,980
bit confused then about labeling them,

336
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:09,800
but still,

337
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,300
we can imagine systems with infinitely many particles,

338
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:13,540
filling all of space,

339
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:15,470
from one end of space

340
00:14:15,470 --> 00:14:17,400
to the other end of space.

341
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,190
But let's stick for the

342
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:22,300
moment with finitely many of them.

343
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:25,940
And the other thing we need to know

344
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:28,800
in order to get started with a system,

345
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:30,740
and to predict its future,

346
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:33,120
is the velocities,

347
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,020
which means the time derivatives,

348
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:36,830
or the rate of change of

349
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:38,640
the Qs with respect to time.

350
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,580
Q sub i dot,

351
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:41,660
time derivative.

352
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:45,500
So Q sub i's are typically functions of time,

353
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,100
as are the time derivatives,

354
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,560
and one,

355
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:51,660
the time derivatives are just gotten

356
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:53,760
by differentiating with respect to time.

357
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:56,260
Alright,

358
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:57,160
the laws of physics,

359
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:58,160
and as far as we know,

360
00:14:58,260 --> 00:15:00,300
all of the laws of physics that we know,

361
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,520
all the basic laws of physics,

362
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,560
Newton's laws,

363
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:08,280
electromagnetic theory,

364
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,320
Einstein's law,

365
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,300
Einstein and Newton's laws of gravity,

