00:15:37,060 --> 00:15:40,000
let's put a couple of horizontal directions in,

378
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:43,640
but the horizontal directions really stand for

379
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:47,140
all the possible Qs of a system.

380
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,300
So the horizontal directions don't

381
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:51,040
have to be three-dimensional space,

382
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:54,410
they could be 300,000 dimensional space if

383
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:57,400
there were 300,000 particles moving on a line.

384
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,280
It simply represents the various coordinates Q1,

385
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:01,860
Q2,

386
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:02,400
Q3,

387
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,080
and so forth,

388
00:16:03,959 --> 00:16:06,960
and specifying a set of Qs,

389
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:07,640
at the beginning,

390
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:08,400
for example,

391
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:16,240
means starting at a point on the space of Qs.

392
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:23,680
So an initial condition corresponds to a set of Qs,

393
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,100
which is a point in this space,

394
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:27,220
and a set of Q dots.

395
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:31,060
The set of Q dots tells you the way

396
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:34,440
the point is moving at initial time equals zero,

397
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:37,130
so it gives you some idea of the

398
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:39,820
direction that the various Qs are moving off in.

399
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:43,080
That's the starting point.

400
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:45,680
System described by Qs and Q dots.

401
00:16:46,580 --> 00:16:51,580
The principle of least action says that you can determine,

402
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:52,360
not that you can,

403
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,740
but the trajectory of all systems,

404
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,360
the trajectory means its history,

405
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:00,740
its history starting with some initial configuration

406
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:04,020
and ending with some final configuration,

407
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,079
incidentally,

408
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:09,900
the word configuration refers to the Qs.

409
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,180
It's a technical term.

410
00:17:11,420 --> 00:17:14,660
It means the values of a set of Qs.

411
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:16,880
It does not mean a set of Q dots.

412
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,540
So when one speaks about a configuration,

413
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:20,839
it means,

414
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:21,780
for example,

415
00:17:21,780 --> 00:17:24,780
fixing the location of all the particles

416
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,780
without fixing their velocity.

417
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:28,220
So that word configuration,

418
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:29,200
keep in mind.

419
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:31,740
We might ask,

420
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:34,420
given that a system starts at one point,

421
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,240
at one configuration,

422
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:39,280
and ends after a time t at another configuration,

423
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:41,260
exactly how does it move in between?

424
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:46,830
What's the path that it

425
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:49,440
takes through the configuration space?

426
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,740
How does it move with time?

427
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:54,840
And the answer is every known system

428
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:58,520
satisfies the principle of least action,

429
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:02,080
which means that there's an expression called the action,

430
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,650
which is built up out of

431
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:06,260
the Q dots and the Qs,

432
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,080
which is minimized,

433
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:12,840
which achieves the minimum value that it can take on

434
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,860
along the trajectory.

435
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:20,080
Physically allowable trajectories are minima of the action.

436
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:20,980
Now what is the action?

437
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,180
The action always has the

438
00:18:24,180 --> 00:18:26,720
form of an integral over time,

439
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,620
dt,

440
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:31,360
of something that's called a Lagrangian.

441
00:18:32,179 --> 00:18:34,329
The Lagrangian is something that's made out

442
00:18:34,329 --> 00:18:36,480
of the Qs and the Q dots.

443
00:18:38,319 --> 00:18:40,800
So it's some Lagrangian,

444
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:43,760
which depends on Q and Q dot,

445
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:47,580
and one speaks about the action

446
00:18:47,580 --> 00:18:49,920
between the initial and final configuration.

447
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:52,960
So that means the integral

448
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,260
is from some initial time t1

449
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:57,660
to some final time t2,

450
00:18:58,379 --> 00:19:00,740
and the trajectories that we explore,

451
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:03,000
the trajectories that we're going to explore,

452
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:06,320
the different trajectories that we're going to compare

453
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:07,980
to find the one of least action,

454
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:12,200
are all trajectories which pass through the same two points.

455
00:19:13,060 --> 00:19:16,300
So we specify a problem by specifying an initial

456
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,940
and a final configuration,

457
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:20,340
and asking which of the

458
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:22,260
many trajectories will minimize the action.

459
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:23,520
Alright,

460
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,260
now what is this thing called the Lagrangian?

461
00:19:25,420 --> 00:19:26,260
As I said,

462
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:27,760
the Lagrangian is just a function

463
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:29,020
of

464
00:19:29,020 --> 00:19:31,760
the coordinates and the velocities,

465
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:33,860
and it typically has,

466
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,140
not always,

467
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:36,620
not always,

468
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:40,440
but it typically has a simple form

469
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,460
consisting of a

470
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:44,620
kinetic energy,

471
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:45,120
t,

472
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:47,900
which depends on the Q dots,

473
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,900
and I'll write down an example in a moment,

474
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:52,000
minus a potential energy.

475
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:56,940
The potential energy only depends on the Qs.

476
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:58,980
It does not depend on the Q dots at all.

477
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:00,520
It depends on position,

478
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,820
but not velocity.

479
00:20:03,260 --> 00:20:07,420
The kinetic energy sometimes depends on both.

480
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:11,060
The simplest systems that we can think about,

481
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,800
particles moving and so forth,

482
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,890
the kinetic energy as a

483
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:16,820
rule depends only on the velocities.

484
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,240
And so,

485
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:18,800
for example,

486
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:21,540
if Q actually represented,

487
00:20:21,740 --> 00:20:26,580
if the Qs represented points moving on a line,

488
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,740
let's imagine points moving on a line,

